Comment: I see their are comments suggesting there is no love interest due to feminism ideals. However this has nothing to do with feminism. Moana is a film based on traditional Polynesian cultures of the South Pacific, where it is strictly forbidden for teenage girls of Moana's age to associate with the opposite sex in a romantic way. This cultural custom applies right until they come of age. So I guess in this case it is more out of respect on Disney's part to follow suit and apply this understanding to the film which in turn brings a level of authenticity to it.
